    "competition": "NEARBY EXTERNAL COMPETITION (from Google Maps):\n- Sydney Auto Service Centre\n- OFFROAD MASTERS \n- RPM Auto Maintenance\n→ Industrial area behind station with multiple auto service competitors\n\nINTERNAL LAYOUT ISSUE:\nADNOC Lube in the middle - \"provides or presents us with a lot of logistical problems\" (Mounir's exact words)\n\nSame pattern as SS761 and SS799.",
    "assessment_notes": "SITE ASSESSMENT (Feb 2, 2026):\n\nMOUNIR'S ASSESSMENT:\n> \"Al Wasit site 657 is off of a highway of sorts. There is again a car wash and vacuum bay for rent. There is an ADNOC Lube in the middle of it, which provides or presents us with a lot of logistical problems. Unless we do a car wash there is not much around. There is a mosque nearby, but then empty land and power stations, it seems, in the vicinity. Further behind the gas station, you can see on the screenshots that there are auto service repairs, so I assume that is an industrial area over there as well.\"\n\nAVAILABLE FOR RENT:\n✓ Car wash\n✓ Vacuum bay\n\nNOT AVAILABLE:\n✗ ADNOC Lube (in the middle) - CRITICAL ISSUE\n\nLAYOUT PROBLEM - THIRD SITE WITH THIS ISSUE:\nADNOC Lube in the middle \"provides or presents us with a lot of logistical problems\"\n\nThis is the THIRD Sharjah site with \"something in the middle\" blocking optimal layout:\n1. SS799: Bridgestone + ADNOC Lube in middle\n2. SS761: ADNOC Lube in middle \n3. SS657: ADNOC Lube in middle\n\nPattern confirmed: Many Sharjah ADNOC sites have central obstructions.\n\nACCESSIBILITY:\n- Off highway (multi-step access)\n- Rating: 2.5/5\n\nSURROUNDING AREA (POOR):\n- Mosque nearby\n- Empty land\n- Power stations in vicinity\n- Industrial area behind with auto service competitors\n- NOT residential\n- NOT commercial/retail\n- Rating: 2.0/5\n\nLIMITED SCOPE:\n\"Unless we do a car wash there is not much around\" - Mounir\n\nThis means:\n- Limited to car wash operation only\n- No broader quick service potential\n- Worse than SS179 (which at least had residential nearby)\n\nNEARBY COMPETITION (from Google Maps):\n- Sydney Auto Service Centre (close by)\n- OFFROAD MASTERS (close by)\n- RPM Auto Maintenance (close by)\n→ Industrial area behind station = auto service cluster\n\nPOSITIVES:\n- Modern, well-maintained facility (good visual quality)\n- Vacuum bay available\n- Car wash available\n- Active traffic visible in photos\n\nNEGATIVES:\n- ADNOC Lube in middle creates logistical problems (critical issue)\n- Off highway access\n- Poor surrounding area: empty land, power stations, industrial behind\n- Limited scope: \"unless we do a car wash there is not much around\"\n- External competition from nearby auto service centers\n- Not residential or commercial retail area\n\nCOMPARISON TO OTHER SITES:\n- Similar facility quality to SS761 (modern, clean)\n- Same fatal flaw: ADNOC Lube in middle\n- Worse location than SS761 (power stations vs. industrial warehouses)\n- Much worse than SS179 (which had residential demographics)\n\nVISUAL OBSERVATIONS (3 photos + 2 videos + 1 map):\n- Modern ADNOC facility with excellent visual presentation\n- Vacuum Bay, ADNOC Lube, ADNOC Oasis visible\n- Large forecourt, active evening traffic\n- Google Maps shows industrial area behind with competitors\n\nRating: 2.5/5\nRecommendation: No Go\n\nRATIONALE FOR No Go:\nDespite modern facility and good visual quality, the combination of:\n1. ADNOC Lube in middle (logistical problems)\n2. Limited scope (car wash only viable per Mounir)\n3. Poor surrounding area (empty land, power stations, industrial)\n4. Off highway access\n5. Nearby external competition\n\n...makes this site operationally challenging and strategically weak. The \"ADNOC Lube in middle\" pattern is proving to be a deal-breaker across multiple Sharjah sites.",
